<subSubSection id="C3236573043FFFF8FF7FF93BFCE67687" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8636F8043FFFF8FF7FF93BFCE67687" blockId="13.[151,1436,1734,2013]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA043FFFF8FF7FF93BFEC177F2" bold="true" box="[151,266,1734,1760]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Female with head and antennal flagellum dark brown to black, mesosoma yellowish-brown, gaster brown (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043FFFF8FF07F916FEBF7614" box="[239,372,1770,1798]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-80@12.[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 13–14. D. pedunculata; 13 body in dorsal view, paratype; 14 body in lateral view, paratype; 15–16. D. pilosa; 15 body in lateral view, holotype; 16 body in dorsal view, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592898/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
), male with head and mesosoma dark brown to black (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043FFFF8FC03F916FBBA7617" box="[1003,1137,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–24" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-39@15.[151,1435,237,1771]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 21–24. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 21–22. D. pilosa; 21 body in lateral view, paratype; 22 body in dorsal view, paratype; 23–24. D. costulata; 23 body in dorsal view, paratype; 24 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592902/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Figs 21, 22</figureCitation>
); fore wing infumate with part below stigmal vein slightly darker (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043FFFF8FDB6F8F2FD78763B" box="[606,691,1806,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-80@12.[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 13–14. D. pedunculata; 13 body in dorsal view, paratype; 14 body in lateral view, paratype; 15–16. D. pilosa; 15 body in lateral view, holotype; 16 body in dorsal view, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592898/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); pronotal collar without a carina along anterior margin (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043FFFF8FAD2F8F2FA457638" box="[1338,1422,1807,1834]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-80@12.[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 13–14. D. pedunculata; 13 body in dorsal view, paratype; 14 body in lateral view, paratype; 15–16. D. pilosa; 15 body in lateral view, holotype; 16 body in dorsal view, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592898/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); midlobe of mesoscutum with four pairs of setae (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043FFFF8FD5FF8CEFCC1765C" box="[695,778,1843,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-80@12.[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 13–14. D. pedunculata; 13 body in dorsal view, paratype; 14 body in lateral view, paratype; 15–16. D. pilosa; 15 body in lateral view, holotype; 16 body in dorsal view, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592898/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); mesoscutellum with sublateral grooves slightly sinuate in lateral part, not joining in posterior part (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043FFFF8FDB2F8AAFD7B7663" box="[602,688,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-80@12.[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 13–14. D. pedunculata; 13 body in dorsal view, paratype; 14 body in lateral view, paratype; 15–16. D. pilosa; 15 body in lateral view, holotype; 16 body in dorsal view, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592898/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Figs 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043FFFF8FD53F8AAFD107663" box="[699,731,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–24" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1794,1818]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-39@15.[151,1435,237,1771]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 21–24. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., males; 21–22. D. pilosa; 21 body in lateral view, paratype; 22 body in dorsal view, paratype; 23–24. D. costulata; 23 body in dorsal view, paratype; 24 body in lateral view, paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592902/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">22</figureCitation>
); fore wing with 25+ scattered setae on ventral surface of costal cell, and with 15 setae along apico-dorsal margin (
<figureCitation id="13022A7D043FFFF8FD24F886FCEB7687" box="[716,800,1914,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-80@12.[151,1435,273,1845]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. Diglyphomorphomyia spp. nov., females; 13–14. D. pedunculata; 13 body in dorsal view, paratype; 14 body in lateral view, paratype; 15–16. D. pilosa; 15 body in lateral view, holotype; 16 body in dorsal view, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592898/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3236573043FFFE7FF2FF863FE6F70BF" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="339" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8636F8043FFFFBFF2FF863FF357053" blockId="13.[151,1436,1734,2013]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1437,151,321]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="335" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis id="B94DEAEA043FFFF8FF2FF863FDFC76AA" bold="true" box="[199,567,1950,1976]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
Description (female 
<typeStatus id="5482885A043FFFF8FE28F863FDE176AA" box="[448,554,1950,1976]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CC19B1D043FFFF8FD74F862FD2576AB" box="[668,750,1951,1977]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="13" pageNumber="334" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9mm</quantity>
. Frons and vertex with weak reticulation, antennal scrobes smooth. Pronotal collar without a carina along anterior margin. Mesoscutum with weak reticulation; midlobe with four pairs of setae, three pairs are long and strong and one pair is short and weak. Mesoscutellum, axillae, dorsellum and propodeum smooth, without reticulation; mesoscutellum with sublateral grooves not joining in posterior part; propodeal callus with nine setae. Fore wing with nine setae on dorsal surface of submarginal vein; with 17 admarginal setae; costal cell with 25+ scattered setae on ventral surface, apico-dorsal margin with 15 setae. Gaster elongate.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF466670043CFFFBFF7FF8E1FAD6764A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592900" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6592900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592900/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="335" startId="14.[151,264,1820,1844]" targetBox="[151,1435,345,1797]" targetPageId="14">
